PENSION EXPENSE IS ALSO SENSITIVE TO CHANGES IN THE EXPECTED LONG-TERM RATE OF ASSET RETURN. A DECREASE OR INCREASE OF 25 BASIS POINTS

IN THE EXPECTED LONG-TERM RATE OF ASSET RETURN WOULD HAVE INCREASED OR DECREASED 2010 NET PERIODIC PENSION EXPENSE BY $123 MILLION.

DIFFERENCES BETWEEN

